Full Description: Top quality trust worthy work is what we believe every homeowner deserves. Combined, the three founders of Handy HomePros have over 90 years of service business experience. We built successful businesses in the past. Our philosophy then was the same as now. If you are the cheapest you’re probably are not the best. When a contractor charges too little he will often cut corners and the end result is sub- standard work. If you take all the variables out of the equation, everyone wants the lowest price possible. At Handy HomePros we look at every variable (years of experience, customer satisfaction, licenses, insurance, proper equipment, code of ethics, etc…). Some handymen ignore some or all of the variables. They put on a smile and a friendly disposition and proceed to con homeowners with “a great deal”. We want quality work at a fair price. Our handymen, tradesmen and contractors are all independent. They are free to charge what they want. Smart business men know what the fair price is for their service. The best provide that service at a fair price and then deliver the extras. Extras like, promptly returning a phone call, keeping the worksite clean, thoroughly explaining options, empathy for the client, arriving when they say they will, providing accurate completion dates, keeping the client informed, avoiding surprise fees, etc… At Handy HomePros we are on a constant search for the best.

Description: ENDWI Campaign was created to help reduce the number of drunk driving-related crashes and fatalities on our roadways.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: The New Mexico Department of Transportation (NMDOT) has been on the cutting edge in using technology to educate the public about the dangers of drinking and driving. With this VR experience they are taking the next step to engage a tech-savvy demographic with an innovative creative approach. Professor Jeremy Bailenson who does research on virtual reality at Stanford University, “In general, their findings show that VR causes more behavior change, causes more engagement, causes more influence than other types of traditional media.” Virtual reality can help to cultivate empathy and lead to better decision making. VR can generate retention rates as high as 90%*. Traditional methods such as classroom discussion, PowerPoint and video only give retention rates in the 30-50% range. Due to a concerted effort between law enforcement, public awareness campaigns, and legislative changes, DWI-related fatalities in New Mexico have been reduced by over 45% since 2006. The ENDWI VR Experience is NMDOT’s latest effort to reduce these numbers, because even one DWI-related injury or fatality is too many.

The software is capable of analyzing a broad range of organic compounds.   As a fast and accurate physiochemical property calculator, SPARC fulfills an important need for the chemical and pharmaceutical market. With more than 5,700 registered users, the software is now in wide use in laboratories in academic, government, and industrial research.   Along with research and development labs, ARChem is marketing SPARC to regulatory agencies in the U.S., Canada, and Europe, which can benefit greatly from the time and cost savings SPARC offers in assessing safety.
